<br>
In the low thirties, you can gain a bub an hour here.  Easy.  You'll blow trough about 50% of your mana and 30% of your pet's health per kill.  Make sure you Flameshield your pet, it'll go much easier.<br>
<br>
As you go over 34, you'll go through 20-30% mana and 10-15% of your pet's health per kill.  You'll be gaining about 3/4 of a bub an hour now, maybe a little less simply because of the higher xp requirements.  Flameshield no longer required.<br>
<br>
The Golra's have NOT had their aggro range increased.  But on two seperate occasions, I have witnessed something strange.  I had just dropped one, and I was medding on the north beach, when one came running out of nowhere and attacked me.  Since I was 35 at the time, he was merely an inconvenience.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   For those of you who don't know, the Golra's are VERY static spawns.  They don't move hardly at all.  All but 2 just stand there, the other 2 pace back and forth about 10 feet.<br>
<br>
On a seperate occasion, this happened to somebody else who was on the island with me.  He wasn't yet 34, so he came running for help.  Free xp for me.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I both cases I believe it is the Golra in the boat on the east shore, as after my encounters with this wanderer, I would continue my pulling of spawns only to see that the Golra in the boat on the east shore was not up when he should have been.  This is merely an FYI.<br>
<br>
There are 10 Golra spawns and 3 Hulking Golra spawns on the island.  At 36 the Hulkings con blue-yellow.  I solo'd a white, but it was too close for comfort.  And the loot is no better.  A group of 3 in the low 30's can down Hulkings fairly easily, but you'll burn through a nice chunk of mana.  Not sure exactly, but you could probably drop 3 normal Golras with the same amount of mana, making the Hulkings inefficient.<br>
<br>
The Hulking Golra on the southeast corner is the placeholder for Halara.  He's a rare spawn, level 40.  He drops some unique items.<br>
<br>
The downsides to this island?<br>
o Should you die, CR is a bitch.  No binding in TD.  BTW, I've never died here.<br>
o The island is small, and can only support a few people.  You may have to fight over spawns, which is a royal pain.<br>
o And finally:  The XP is so steady and easy, it'll make you SOFT...<br>
<br>
Balasarius NoxDominus<br>
36th Circle Mage<br>
